The paper deals with regular path queries on graph databases, which is a topic closely related to database theory and graph theory. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves complexity analysis and automata theory, which are related to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of automata models and regular expressions also suggests a connection to cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
